      "content": "Naproxen is also an NSAID, much like ibuprofen, meaning it carries the same kidney risks. Both medications work by inhibiting prostaglandins, which is what puts stress on your kidneys when you have CKD. Because of this overlapping mechanism, naproxen is not a safer alternative to ibuprofen in this situation. You should stick to acetaminophen or call your doctor's on-call line for advice.",
